    },
    {
      "type": "text",
      "value": "India's economic growth story is increasingly being written in its southern states. Tamil Nadu, Karnataka, Telangana, Andhra Pradesh, and Kerala have transformed from regional players into the nation's primary growth engine, collectively contributing nearly one-third of India's GDP while setting benchmarks in per capita income, industrial output, and technological innovation. According to the Rubix Data Sciences 'State of the States' report (March 2026), southern states increased their combined share of India's GDP from 25% in FY2015 to 27% in FY2025, with the broader southern region accounting for approximately 31% of national output—marginally ahead of the northern region at 30% [citation:1][citation:2][citation:3]."
